nguage\", \"score\": 0.9606426069651294, \"rank\": 0.02051791494839333, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 792, \"end\": 797, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9998709855052126, \"rank\": 0.00012490335028274738, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 808, \"end\": 814, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9606426069651294, \"rank\": 0.02051791494839333, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 864, \"end\": 869, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9998709855052126, \"rank\": 0.00012490335028274738, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 909, \"end\": 927, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ioannis_Fountoulis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ioannis Fountoulis\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ioannis_Fountoulis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ioannis_Fountoulis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The high priestess lit the Panathenaic Stadium cauldron and used the flame to light up a final torch, which she handed to Greek Olympic Committee President Spyros Capralos.\", \"from\": 929, \"to\": 1101, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1051, \"end\": 1074, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hellenic_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Greek Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hellenic_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hellenic_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1085, \"end\": 1100, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spyros_Capralos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Spyros Capralos\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spyros_Capralos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spyros_Capralos\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024 chief Tony Estanguet received the torch from Capralos, which marked the end of the flame's 11-day travel in the Olympics Greek origin.\", \"from\": 1103, \"to\": 1248, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1103, \"end\": 1113, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.236589297164664e-15, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1120, \"end\": 1134, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Leaving Greece on Saturday, the cauldron will travel on the Mediterranean Sea for 12 days as it heads for France's southern port city of Marseille on a 19th century sailing ship, and is expected to arrive on May 8 and welcomed by some 150,000 spectators in a ceremony at the Old Port of Marseille.\", \"from\": 1250, \"to\": 1547, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1356, \"end\": 1362, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9996864587271971, \"rank\": 0.00016510916527550767, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1387, \"end\": 1396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"score\": 0.999999512407049, \"rank\": 4.860643